con:config.script:
import jxl.*
def excelFilePath = "D:\\WebServices\\Parabank_TestData.xls"
File excelFile = new File(excelFilePath)
Workbook wb=Workbook.getWorkbook(excelFile)
Sheet sheet=wb.getSheet(0)
int noOfRows=sheet.getRows()-1//number of rows in the excel
log.info "noOfRows= $noOfRows" for (int rowId in 1..noOfRows){ log.warn'--------------------------------' log.info sheet.getCell(0,rowId).getContents() log.info sheet.getCell(1,rowId).getContents() log.info sheet.getCell(2,rowId).getContents() log.warn'--------------------------------' }
wb.close()

import jxl.*
def TestCase =context.testCase def count def excelFilePath = "D:\\WebServices\\Parabank_TestData.xls"
File excelFile = new File(excelFilePath)
Workbook wb=Workbook.getWorkbook(excelFile)
Sheet sheet=wb.getSheet(0)
int noOfRows=sheet.getRows()-1//number of rows in the excel
PropertiesTestStep=TestCase.getTestStepByName("Properties") count =PropertiesTestStep.getPropertyValue("Counter").toInteger() log.info count log.info "noOfRows= $noOfRows"
//If Total Records is unknown (at start) get the rowcount from Excel
if(PropertiesTestStep.getPropertyValue("Total").toString()=="") PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("Total",noOfRows.toString()) count++
log.info count Cell userName = sheet.getCell(0,count) Cell password = sheet.getCell(1,count) Cell customerId = sheet.getCell(2,count) Cell State = sheet.getCell(3,count) Cell AccountType = sheet.getCell(4,count) log.info ("Count is : "+ count.toString() + "User Name : " +userName.getContents()+"Password : "+password.getContents()+"CustomerId :" + customerId.getContents()+" State : "+State.getContents()+ " AccountType : "+AccountType.getContents()) wb.close()
PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("Username",userName.getContents()) PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("Password",password.getContents()) PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("CustomerId",customerId.getContents()) PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("State",State.getContents()) PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("AccountType",AccountType.getContents()) if(count == PropertiesTestStep.getPropertyValue("Total").toInteger()-1) PropertiesTestStep.setPropertyValue("End","True")

def TestCase =context.testCase PropertiesTestStep =TestCase.getTestStepByName("Properties") Stop = PropertiesTestStep.getPropertyValue("End").toString()
if(Stop=="True") log.info("Exit Groovy Script --DataLoop") else testRunner.gotoStepByName("Groovy Script")
